---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Gardening — Grow Your Score with Garden Terms"
  description="Gardening words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. THYME (13pts), SHRUB (10pts), TOPIARY (12pts), MULCH (12pts). Botanical vocabulary for competitive players."
  keywords="scrabble gardening words, thyme scrabble points, shrub scrabble, topiary scrabble, mulch scrabble word, garden terms scrabble, botanical words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Gardening — Grow Your Score with Garden Terms","description":"Gardening words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. THYME (13pts), SHRUB (10pts), TOPIARY (12pts), MULCH (12pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-gardening"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is TOPIARY a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! TOPIARY scores 12 points (T=1, O=1, P=3, I=1, A=1, R=1, Y=4) as a 7-letter word. It means the art of trimming shrubs into ornamental shapes. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is THYME worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"THYME scores 13 points (T=1, H=4, Y=4, M=3, E=1). It's one of the highest-scoring 5-letter gardening words thanks to the H and Y tiles."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is MULCH valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! MULCH scores 12 points (M=3, U=1, L=1, C=3, H=4). It means a protective ground covering and is valid in all official Scrabble dictionaries."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Gardening — Grow Your Score with Garden Terms</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The garden is surprisingly fertile ground for Scrabble players. Horticultural terms pack H, Y, and M tiles — mid-value letters that combine beautifully into 10-15 point words. From trimming hedges to spreading mulch, these everyday garden activities translate directly into board-winning vocabulary.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">THYME (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TOPIARY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MULCH</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SHRUB</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Garden Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">THYME — 13 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">T=1, H=4, Y=4, M=3, E=1 · 5 letters · Uses H+Y combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A fragrant herb used in cooking and gardens alike. THYME gets its power from the H=4 and Y=4 combination, delivering 13 points from just 5 tiles — that's 2.6 points per tile, an excellent ratio for a common word.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌿 TOPIARY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · T=1, O=1, P=3, I=1, A=1, R=1, Y=4 · Shaped shrubs</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍂 MULCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · M=3, U=1, L=1, C=3, H=4 · Ground cover</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌳 SHRUB</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · S=1, H=4, R=1, U=1, B=3 · Small bush</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪴 PRUNE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · P=3, R=1, U=1, N=1, E=1 · Trim branches</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Valid Garden Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>These everyday gardening terms are all playable in competitive Scrabble:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COMPOST</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TROWEL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WEED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LOAM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GRAFT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOWER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Garden Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MULCH clears difficult racks:</span> When you hold M+C+H together (total 10 from those three alone), MULCH lets you dump them all in one efficient 12-point play.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SHRUB hooks into SHRUBS:</span> SHRUB (10pts) becomes SHRUBS (11pts) with a simple S-hook. Play SHRUB near an open lane for the extension.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TOPIARY for bingo setups:</span> At 7 letters, TOPIARY uses all your tiles if you draw perfectly — 12 points plus the 50-point bingo bonus for 62 total.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Garden words excel at combining <span class="text-white font-medium">H (4pts) and Y (4pts)</span> with common letters. THYME, SHRUB, and MULCH all leverage H alongside another mid-value tile, consistently scoring 10-13 from compact 5-letter plays.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-cooking/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Cooking</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/nature-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Nature Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-gardening-flowers/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Flower Words Valid in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid gardening word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
